# 2026-06-14 05:40:56.622202
+We are continuing the development of our Notion Clone MVP. In our last session, you successfully updated the database for NextAuth, Export/Import, and Image support, but you were interrupted before finishing the UI and fixing some bugs. Also, to temporarily test the app, I modified `src/app/api/documents/route.ts` by commenting out the session checks and hardcoding `sessionId: "anonymous"`.
+
+Please implement the following comprehensive updates step-by-step. STRICTLY use the Aider file edit format (bare filename on line 1, ``` on line 2, and the full untruncated code block):
+
+**PHASE 0: Cleanup & Restore Auth API**
+- Update `src/app/api/documents/route.ts`: Remove the `sessionId: "anonymous"` hacks and my commented-out code. Restore the proper NextAuth validation (e.g., `getServerSession`) for GET, POST, PATCH, and DELETE routes. Ensure document operations are strictly tied to the logged-in user's ID/Session.
+
+**PHASE 1: Fix Interrupted Auth UI & Image Bug**
+- Update `AppShell.tsx` and `Sidebar.tsx`: Add a section at the bottom of the Sidebar showing the logged-in user's email and a "Sign Out" button. If not logged in, show a "Sign In" button (redirecting to `/login` or handling Auth.js sign-in).
+- Update `Editor.tsx`: Fix the TipTap image bug where typing next to an image deletes it. Ensure the Image extension is configured correctly (e.g., `inline: true` or standard block behavior that allows adding text below it).
+
+**PHASE 2: Workspaces (Database & UI)**
+- Update `prisma/schema.prisma`: Add a `Workspace` model (id, name, userId). Update the `Document` model to belong to a `Workspace` (`workspaceId`).
+- UI (`Sidebar.tsx`): Add a Workspace Switcher dropdown at the top of the Sidebar (like Notion). Users should be able to create a new workspace and switch between them.
+- API: Update document fetching and creating logic to strictly filter by the currently active `workspaceId`.
+
+**PHASE 3: Drag and Drop Categories**
+- Assume I have installed `@hello-pangea/dnd`.
+- Update `Sidebar.tsx` and `DocumentTree.tsx`: Implement drag-and-drop functionality so users can drag documents into different categories or reorder them within the sidebar.
+
+**PHASE 4: Dark Mode & Advanced Notion Features**
+- Dark Mode: Assume `next-themes` is installed. Wrap the app with `ThemeProvider` in `layout.tsx`. Add a Theme Toggle button to the Sidebar. Apply Tailwind dark classes (e.g., `dark:bg-neutral-900`) across all components.
+- Advanced Editor (`Editor.tsx`): Add `@tiptap/extension-task-list`, `@tiptap/extension-task-item`, and `@tiptap/extension-code-block-lowlight`. 
+- Slash Commands: Add TipTap's `FloatingMenu` that appears on empty lines to quickly insert Headings, Bullet Lists, and Task Lists.
+
+Execute these phases carefully. If you need to stop and ask for confirmation after modifying the Prisma schema, you can do so.

