# 2026-06-14 05:44:47.008586
+You are completely right to ask. Because our previous session crashed exactly during the NextAuth setup, those files were NEVER created. The Prisma schema was only partially updated (only `sessionId` was added to `Document`), and the User models were never added. 
+
+There is no `auth.ts`, no NextAuth route handler, and no `login` page yet.
+
+Please treat this as a fresh NextAuth setup. Here is what you need to do before starting PHASE 0:
+1. Update `prisma/schema.prisma` to include standard NextAuth models (`User`, `Account`, `Session`, etc.). Add a `password` string field to the `User` model for Credentials auth.
+2. Create the NextAuth v4 route handler `src/app/api/auth/[...nextauth]/route.ts` using the Credentials provider (with bcryptjs for password hashing).
+3. Create a basic `src/app/login/page.tsx` (and optionally a register page) so users can sign in.
+4. After creating these, proceed with PHASE 0, treating NextAuth as the source of truth instead of the old localStorage hack.
+
+Please execute these missing setup steps first, ask me to run `npx prisma db push`, and then proceed with the rest of the PHASES.

