+1. Check the `prisma/schema.prisma` file. Ensure the `Page` or `Document` model supports a hierarchical nested structure (parent-child relationship for subpages):
+   - Must have an optional `parentId String?` and a relation pointing back to itself: `parent Page? @relation("SubPages", fields: [parentId], references: [id], onDelete: Cascade)`
+   - Must have `children Page[] @relation("SubPages")`
+2. Ensure fields like `title` (String), `content` (String/Json?), `isArchived` (Boolean), and `isPublished` (Boolean) are present.
+3. If any database fields are missing or changed, write the schema and run/instruct the local migration (`npx prisma db push` or `npx prisma migrate dev`).
+
+---
+
+STEP 2: STATE MANAGEMENT & SIDEBAR COMPLETION (UI/UX Layer)
+1. Complete the functional Sidebar component. It must dynamically fetch and render the list of pages from the Prisma database using Next.js Server Actions or API Routes.
+2. Implement recursive rendering for nested subpages within the sidebar (collapsible tree view support).
+3. The Sidebar must handle:
+   - "Create New Page" button triggering an optimistic UI update or immediate loading state while hitting the database.
+   - Active page highligting based on the current URL router path.
+   - Expand/Collapse toggles for pages that have children, persisting the open/close state in React context or local storage.
+
+---
+
+STEP 3: PAGE-MANAGEMENT ROUTING & CONTROLLERS (Routing Layer)
+1. Complete the dynamic routing structure under `app/(main)/pages/[pageId]/page.tsx` (or your equivalent active main directory).
+2. Ensure proper error routing: If `pageId` does not exist in Prisma, gracefully redirect or show a clean 404/not-found state.
+3. Implement Server Actions or API routes for:
+   - Creating a blank page/subpage.
+   - Deleting a page (handling cascade deletion or unlinking of child pages safely).
+   - Renaming a page title directly from the sidebar or the main header view, ensuring the sidebar reflects the new title instantly without a full page reload.
+
+---
